data.title: Grace Foo ✨
data.content:
#NewSelfWales I think the reason why I love this picture so much is because this is one of the only times my soul is visible in my physical appearance, captured on camera. I can never express how I always felt I'm born in the wrong era- that I do things the old-fashioned way, I write on my typewriter, I hold values of the past.
.
.
My all time fave film Midnight in Paris (swipe) whisked me off on a time travel to the 1920s era. This film, it opens up a visual feast- so picturesque, imaginative, charming. Something realists would tell you to snap out of. But I just like to see the world like that, through those dreamy lens- dancing in the streets of Paris in the rain, live music in a pub, living as a broke artist but it's alright cos you have the antidote to the emptiness of existence. This film is literally how I see life. If you want to see life through my eyes watch this film.
.
.
.
